\section{Mayer-Vietoris LES short-complex infrastructure (iter-019)}
\label{sec:hmodule_prime_mayer_vietoris_short_complex}

Iter-019 lays the carrier of the eventual $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)$-flavored short exact sequence on which the connecting hom $\delta$ of the Mayer-Vietoris LES is built. The short complex is a direct mirror of Mathlib's $\AddCommGrpCat$-flavored \lstinline{MayerVietorisSquare.shortComplex} (\texttt{MayerVietorisSquare.lean} L234--249), with $\AddCommGrpCat.\free$ replaced by $\ModuleCat.\free\,k$. The infrastructure decomposes into three declarations: a one-line Mathlib gap-fill instance, a pushout-of-free-sheaves analog (lemma), and the short-complex carrier (definition).

\subsection{Mathlib gap and the helper instance}

Mathlib registers $(\AddCommGrpCat.\free).\IsLeftAdjoint$ in \lstinline{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/Grp/Adjunctions.lean} L84 as a typeclass instance, enabling $\Sheaf.\composeAndSheafify\,J\,\AddCommGrpCat.\free$ to acquire the necessary $\PreservesColimit$ instance. Mathlib's \lstinline{ModuleCat/Adjunctions.lean} provides the adjunction \lstinline{ModuleCat.adj k : ModuleCat.free k ⊣ forget (ModuleCat k)} but does not register the corresponding $\IsLeftAdjoint$ instance (that registration lives only in \lstinline{ModuleCat/Topology/Basic.lean} for topological modules, an unrelated context). This is a real Mathlib gap on the path to a $\ModuleCat\,k$-flavored Mayer-Vietoris LES.

